# Electronics & Control
## Home Theater System - Rev 5.2 Extract

**Document Purpose:** AV processor, amplification, signal flow, and calibration.

**Source:** Extracted from Home_Theater_System_Complete_Design_Rev5_2.md

---

## Electronics & Control

### AV Processor

**Model:** Marantz AV10
- Channels: 9.4.6 processing capability
- Bass management: 4 independent subwoofer outputs (Dirac ART)
- Room correction: Dirac Live + Dirac Bass Control + Dirac ART
- Connectivity: HDMI 2.1, full 8K support (future-proof)
- Outputs: Balanced XLR preferred for main channels
- Location: Equipment rack on front stage

### Amplification Summary

**Main Channels (LCR):**
- Amplifier: Buckeye Hypex NcX500 (rack-mounted, multi-channel)
- Power: 500W @ 4Ω per channel
- Channels needed: 3 (L, C, R)
- Location: Equipment rack on front stage

**Surround & Atmos Channels:**
- Amplifier: Buckeye Hypex NC252MP (rack-mounted, multi-channel)
- Power: 200W @ 4Ω per channel (adequate for 96dB sensitivity HT-12s)
- Channels needed: 2 (side surrounds) + 2 (rear surrounds) + 6 (Atmos) = 10 total
- Configuration: Multiple NC252MP units or single 10+ channel unit
- Location: Equipment rack on front stage

**Subwoofers:**
- Amplifier: Buckeye NC502MP (4-channel, rack-mounted)
- Power: 450W @ 2Ω per channel
- Channels: 4 (one per subwoofer)
- Location: Equipment rack on front stage

**Crowson Transducers:**
- Amplifier: Buckeye NC252MP (6-channel, rack-mounted)
- Power: ~160W @ 8Ω per channel
- Channels: 6 (one per transducer)
- Location: Equipment rack on front stage

**All amplifiers:**
- Class D topology (efficient, cool-running)
- Rack mountable for clean installation
- Hypex NCore technology (low distortion, high damping factor)

